     <TD width="100%">
      <div align="Left">
<!---------------------------->
<table cellpadding=2 cellspacing=2>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Recommended Level<br>for starting quest:</b></td><td valign="bottom"> 62<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting zone:</b></td><td valign="top"> Plane of Tranquility<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Additional zones:</b></td><td valign="top"> Bastion of Thunder, Halls of Honor, Tower of Solusek Ro, Plane of Tactics<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting NPC:</b></td><td valign="top"> Bor Warhammer<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Reward:</b></td><td valign="top"> Armor of Emblazoned Souls<br><br></td></tr>
</table>

In order to start this quest you <i>must</i> be either level 62+ or be flagged for any of the Tier 3 zones (Plane of Tactics counts a Tier 3 for the purpose of this quest).<br>
<br>
You can find Bor Warhammer in one of the buildings behind the bank in Plane of Tranquility.<br>
<br>
You say, 'Hail, Bor Warhammer'<br>
<br>
Bor Wharhammer says 'Greetin's t'ye Rozzl! Isn't the area 'round 'ere so nice an' quiet? Such a departure from me old days; slaving o'er the forge t'create masterpieces! T'be 'onest, at times I do miss the old forge, but after I created me finest breastplate, it seemed as if nothing else I made could ever live up t'it. So I left me home to'wander the land an' see what I could learn o'the world. I 'ave learned quite a bit from the elders 'ere an' the skilled craftspeople in New Tanaan. I 'ave even devised a type o'emblem that will impart the magic o'tranquility into the user t'create planar armors from pieces o'energy found in the planes.'<br>
<br>
You say, 'what emblem?' <br>
<br>
Bor Wharhammer says 'Well, the emblems dinnae be easy t'craft but I will gladly give ye one fer the price of 500 platinum pieces. They allow a planes traveler with no craftin' skills t'create many fine pieces o'planar armor in a special, magical kit I also 'ave an' will throw in with the price. The kit acts as a focal point fer the wild magic energy o'the Planes. Ye will only be able t'use each emblem an' kit once when ye create the piece, 'owever I dinnae be goin' anywhere soon! Just venture back when ye need another an' dinnae ferget the coin! <br>
<br>
You say, 'What plate armor?' <br>
<br>
Bor Wharhammer says 'Ahhhhh Radric! The fine rigid armor that can stop a shaft from piercing yer heart! Too bad it be so cumbersome an' difficult t'move about in. To construct a piece o'plate armor, ye need t'combine a plate mold, an emblem, various amounts o'sheet metal an' use one o'those crafty Tanaan smithin' 'ammers all within a furnace touched by Ro. Ethereal metal sheet construction is another matter. Ye will need t'combine two bricks o'ethereal energy, an ethereal temper an' a Tanaan smithin' 'ammer within a Tanaan forge. I would seek a skilled craftsperson t'make the metal sheets fer ye; the emblem will enable ye t'craft the final armor piece no matter what yer skill be. '<br>
<br>
At this point hand Bor 500 platinum and he will give you a Mystical Furnace of Ro (a container that looks like a forge) and a Shadowknight emblem.<br>
<br>
From here, you need to find Ornate molds which drop in any of the planes listed above.  Usually the molds can be found on named trash or zone mini-bosses (for instance Icestorm, in Bastion of Thunder, drops the breastplate mold).  Then you need Ethereal Sheets of metal.  The number of sheets you need depends on the piece you are making.  Bracer requires 1, Breastplate requires 3, etc.  The number of sheets you need are the same you would need of other material for making any plate armor.<br>
<br>
The last thing you need is a Tanaan smithing hammer.  You can purchase this near the forge in the far west edge of the Plane of Tranquility.  It costs a little more than 100 platinum, but you get the hammer back.<br>
<br>
Finally, combine all those things in the Mystical Furnace of Ro.  You can <b>not</b> fail on this combine regardless of your skill in smithing.  You will then receive your armor, as well as the smithing hammer.  A new emblem will have to be "purchased" for every piece you wish to make.<br>
<br>
I'll try to get the stats into the armor set list as soon as I can.<br>

